sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant OAuth as OpenShift OAuth<br/>Bearer Token
    participant Notebook as Notebook Pod<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant DSPApi as DSP API Server<br/>8887/TCP gRPC
    participant Tekton as Tekton Controller<br/>PipelineRun
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant KServe as KServe Controller<br/>Kubernetes API
    participant Knative as Knative Service<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant Istio as Istio Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Predictor as Predictor Pod<br/>8080/TCP mTLS
    participant MLMD as ML Metadata<br/>9090/TCP gRPC
    participant TrustyAI as TrustyAI Service<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>9090/TCP HTTP

    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
        Note over User,Notebook: Workflow 1: Notebook Development & Model Training
        User->>Dashboard: Create Notebook<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (OAuth)
        Dashboard->>OAuth: Validate Token<br/>SubjectAccessReview
        OAuth-->>Dashboard: Token Valid
        Dashboard->>KServe: Create Notebook CR<br/>kubeflow.org/v1
        KServe->>Notebook: Deploy StatefulSet<br/>+ OAuth Proxy Sidecar
        Notebook-->>Dashboard: Route Created<br/>TLS re-encrypt
        User->>Notebook: Access JupyterLab<br/>HTTPS/443 (OAuth)
        Notebook->>S3: Train Model, Save Artifacts<br/>AWS IAM Auth
        S3-->>Notebook: Model Saved
    end

    rect rgb(255, 248, 240)
        Note over User,Prometheus: Workflow 2: Pipeline Execution with Elyra
        User->>Notebook: Author Pipeline<br/>Elyra Extension
        Notebook->>DSPApi: Submit Pipeline<br/>HTTP POST /apis/v1beta1/pipelines
        DSPApi->>Tekton: Create PipelineRun CR<br/>tekton.dev/v1beta1
        Tekton->>S3: Pipeline Steps Execute<br/>Pull/Push Artifacts
        S3-->>Tekton: Artifacts Stored
        Tekton->>MLMD: Record Lineage<br/>gRPC/8080
        MLMD-->>Tekton: Lineage Recorded
        User->>Dashboard: View Pipeline Results<br/>HTTPS/443
        Dashboard->>MLMD: Query Artifacts<br/>gRPC/9090 (Envoy)
        MLMD-->>Dashboard: Artifact Metadata
    end

    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Note over User,Predictor: Workflow 3: Model Deployment with KServe
        User->>Dashboard: Create InferenceService<br/>serving.kserve.io/v1beta1
        Dashboard->>KServe: Apply InferenceService CR
        KServe->>S3: Storage Initializer<br/>Download Model (HTTPS)
        S3-->>KServe: Model Artifacts
        KServe->>Knative: Create Knative Service<br/>serving.knative.dev/v1
        Knative->>Predictor: Deploy Predictor Pod<br/>Scale from zero
        KServe->>Istio: Configure VirtualService<br/>networking.istio.io/v1beta1
        KServe->>KServe: ODH Model Controller<br/>Creates OpenShift Route
        User->>Istio: POST /v1/models/{name}:predict<br/>HTTPS/443, Bearer Token
        Istio->>Predictor: Forward Request<br/>mTLS STRICT, Service Identity
        Predictor-->>Istio: Inference Result<br/>JSON Response
        Istio-->>User: HTTP 200 OK
    end

    rect rgb(255, 240, 255)
        Note over TrustyAI,Prometheus: Workflow 4: Model Fairness Monitoring
        User->>Dashboard: Create TrustyAIService CR
        Dashboard->>TrustyAI: Deploy TrustyAI Pod<br/>+ OAuth Proxy
        TrustyAI->>Predictor: Watch InferenceService<br/>Patch Payload Processor
        Predictor->>TrustyAI: Send Inference Payloads<br/>HTTP/8080
        TrustyAI->>TrustyAI: Calculate Fairness Metrics<br/>SPD, DIR
        TrustyAI->>Prometheus: Expose /q/metrics<br/>HTTP/8080
        Prometheus->>TrustyAI: Scrape Metrics<br/>ServiceMonitor
        User->>Prometheus: Query Fairness Metrics<br/>HTTPS/443 (OAuth)
        Prometheus-->>User: Metrics Dashboard
    end

    rect rgb(255, 255, 240)
        Note over User,S3: Workflow 5: Distributed Ray Job with CodeFlare
        User->>Dashboard: Submit AppWrapper CR<br/>workload.codeflare.dev
        Dashboard->>KServe: MCAD Queue (CodeFlare)
        KServe->>KServe: Check Resource Availability
        KServe->>KServe: Create RayCluster CR<br/>ray.io/v1
        KServe->>S3: Ray Pods Deploy<br/>Head + Workers
        S3->>S3: Ray Head: Distribute Tasks<br/>TCP/10001, GCS/6379
        S3-->>User: Job Results<br/>Ray Dashboard HTTPS/443
    end
